  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering typically involves several key components:\n\n1. International Conventions\n- UN Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Palermo Convention\n- Vienna Convention\n\n2. Key Legislative Acts\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n\n3. Regulatory Bodies\n- Financial Crimes Enforcement Network (FinCEN)\n- Securities and Exchange Commission\n- Central banks\n- Law enforcement agencies\n\n4. Key Legal Principles\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Enhanced scrutiny of high-risk sectors\n\n5. Criminal Penalties\n- Substantial financial fines\n- Asset forfeiture\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Corporate and individual sanctions\n\n6. Compliance Requirements\n- Risk assessment\n- Internal control systems\n- Staff training\n- Regular audits\n- Transaction record-keeping\n\n7. International Cooperation\n- Information sharing\n- Cross-border investigations\n- Extradition agreements\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes.",
